Bosque de Yucca filifera, gently rolling hills of volcanic ash-beds, Suelo gravelly & sandy alluvial soil derived from volcanic ash. Yucca filifera, Larrea tridentata, Flourensia cernua, Opuntia ficus-indica. Growing in fine-sandy to silty brown soil of generally gravelly flat area between low hills; locally abundant but only one restricted population seen.
